{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"709e88c4-edb9-4d34-8a01-f502471a2604","content":"Here are the **evaluation performance issues** in this project:\n\n---\n\n### 1. 🔴 File I/O Property Function (Most Expensive)\n**`EvalHeavy.csproj`, line 13:**\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nThis performs **synchronous file I/O during evaluation**. Property functions like `File::ReadAllText` block the evaluation phase and run on every single evaluation (IDE background evaluations, restores, builds). This is one of the most expensive anti-patterns.\n\n**Fix:** Read the file at build time via a custom target with `Inputs/Outputs`, or use `ReadLinesFromFile` task instead.\n\n---\n\n### 2. 🟠 Expensive Recursive Glob\n**`EvalHeavy.csproj`, line 9:**\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n`**\\*.*` walks the **entire directory tree** on every evaluation. This gets worse as the repo grows (especially if `node_modules`, `.git`, or other large directories exist). The SDK already handles implicit globs for `Compile`, `Content`, etc.\n\n**Fix:** Narrow the glob to specific extensions/directories, or add large directories to `$(DefaultItemExcludes)`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. 🟡 Deep Import Chain\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nA 3-level deep chain of manually imported `.props` files. While 3 levels is manageable, this pattern can become a bottleneck as it grows. Each import adds file I/O and extends the evaluation graph. The imports also use **relative paths without `$(MSBuildThisFileDirectory)`**, making them fragile.\n\n**Fix:** Flatten imports where possible, or consolidate into `Directory.Build.props`.\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| Issue | Severity | Impact |\n|---|---|---|\n| `File::ReadAllText` in property | 🔴 High | Blocks eval with disk I/O every time |\n| `**\\*.*` recursive glob | 🟠 Medium | Walks entire tree each evaluation |\n| 3-level import chain | 🟡 Low | Extra file lookups, fragile paths |\n\nThe **file-reading property function** is the most critical to fix — it runs on every IDE evaluation tick and cannot be cached by MSBuild.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"54f6d014-d8ab-4e54-9b9a-3e5dc4ba28b9","outputTokens":606,"requestId":"C781:203C31:2145F3:2ADE59:69FFDE87"},"id":"992b0487-4404-48be-8062-27d2f4e26de3","timestamp":"2026-05-10T01:25:43.675Z","parentId":"161d6fed-92cf-4e52-b521-d7c955258a2c"}
